f:\mathbb{R}^k \rightarrow \mathbb{R}
\sum_{i=1}^{k} x_i \frac{df}{dx_i}(\mathrm{x} )\ge 0
\mathrm{x}=(x_1,x_2,...,x_k) \in \mathbb{R} ^k
\sum_{i=1}^{k} x_i \frac{df}{dx_i}(\mathrm{x} )= (x_1,x_2,...,x_k) \cdot (\nabla f(x))=\nabla _w f(\mathrm{x})
\nabla _w f(\mathrm{x}) \ge 0
x \in \mathbb R^k
g \colon [0,1] \to \mathbb R
g(t) = f(tx)
g
g'(t) = f'(tx)x
t > 0
g'(t) = \frac 1t f'(tx)tx  = \frac 1t\sum_{i=1}^k\frac{\partial f}{\partial x_i}(tx)tx_i \ge 0
f
f(0)
